First ventrite acuminate between metacoxae; ventrites with fine punctures and sparse semi-erect setae. Legs covered with long semi-erect setae; protibiae with short and fine setae on underside; tarsal formula: I> II+III; protibiae curved; mesotibiae and metatibiae slightly sinuate near base. Parameres of tegmen (
Fig. 16
). Totally fused small parameres with rounded apex and 2 thin brushes of setae at apex.
